{
  "stem": "1354.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "While he painted, he puts them on these nails, and there were ovens, what later on, they were burning out those pots with-- with shelves all from the beginning of the factory to the end, to put in those boards with the pots to get them dry.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my job was to take those boards, and like a waitress, carry them-- carry them to the shelves, and it was very heavy.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then bring back those empty boards to the station where he was painting.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was going on for-- to the end, I-- I already-- later on, when you painted, you know how a pot has a edge on the top?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I advanced, so my job was just to make the edges on them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was hard work, 12 hours a-- a day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Did you-- did they feed you while you were working there?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did they--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got our soups, and-- and-- but my brother was helping me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was in-- going from Plaszow to ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were liquidating over there all the things what the Jewish people left.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was helping himself instead of the Germans to take.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so he was sending me some money always, because our food was coming from Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Jewish policeman were always going with a wagon to bring the food to our-- we belonged really to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so he knew all those Jewish policeman, so he send me money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when the Polish people were coming in, they were bringing for us some bread and butter, and sometimes a piece of meat and eggs.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And being that there was like oven there and there were pots-- because that was the pot vessel-- we could even cook ourselves some things.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
